on the connotations of comfort that surrounded that old chair.";i:13;s:92:"The suggesting of a meaning by a word apart from the thing it explicitly names or describes.";i:14;s:81:"A seat for one person that has a back usually four legs and sometimes two arms 2.";i:15;s:128:"Connotative Meaning Sometimes the writer uses connotative meaning to associate positive negative or neutral emotions with words.";i:16;s:100:"For example the words childish and youthful have same meanings but they have different connotations.";i:17;s:80:"Childish is used as a negative word whereas youthful is used as a positive word.";i:18;s:66:"Symbols can have two types of meaning--Denotative and Connotative.";i:19;s:83:"Denotative Meaning is the meaning of an symbol that is shared by a group of people.";i:20;s:83:"If you say the worddog most English speakers will point to the same type of animal.";i:21;s:64:"Denotative meaning is what makes symbols work for communication.";i:22;s:85:"Connotative Meaning is the meaning of a symbol that is personal to an individual and.";i:23;s:119:"Connotation represents the various social overtones cultural implications or emotional meanings associated with a sign.";i:24;s:68:"Denotation represents the explicit or referential meaning of a sign.";i:25;s:77:"Denotation refers to the literal meaning of a word the dictionary definition.";i:26;s:85:"Connotative meaning of chair Pandemi Strategi Apa yang Bisa Dijalankan Untuk Survive.";i:27;s:110:"Dengan UV Tanaman Lebih Optimal Karena Tanaman Tetap Berfotosintesis Q5 Stik Serbu Bangkalan Pariwisata Jatim.";i:28;s:59:"Meski Dibuka Belum Tetapkan Target Pulih Saja Sudah Untung.";i:29;s:125:"Connotative meaning is everything else people bring to or get out of the word beyond its plain and commonly-accepted sense s.";i:30;s:158:"Connotation comes in allusively it comes in euphemistically it comes in by association - a word heard only in certain contexts will carry that flavor with it.";i:31;s:76:"The Connotative meaning of a word generally cannot be found in a dictionary.";i:32;s:118:"Connotation is any other meaning a word suggests to an individual based on his or her background and past experiences.";i:33;s:104:"Unlike denotative meaning connotative meaning is much more subjective personal and contextual by nature.";i:34;s:95:"A feeling or idea that is suggested by a particular word although it need not be a part of the.";i:35;s:78:"Connotative meaning the emotional reaction engendered in the reader by a word.";i:36;s:27:"Page 4 Referential meaning.";i:37;s:31:"Polysemous has several meaning.";i:38;s:65:"Chair BUT o Semotactic environment or co-text figurative meaning.";i:39;s:18:"Father of a child.";i:40;s:104:"Connotation sets the tone and using one word or another can seriously alter a sentences meaning or tone.";i:41;s:33:"Read the following two sentences.";i:42;s:151:"The woman slammed the door behind her threw her bag on the floor and slumped into a kitchen chair where she poured herself a much-needed glass of wine.";i:43;s:107:"The associated or secondary meaning of a word or expression in addition to its explicit or primary meaning.";i:44;s:74:"A possible connotation of home is a place of warmth comfort and affection.";i:45;s:21:"The act of connoting.";i:46;s:97:"The suggesting of an additional meaning for a word or expression apart from its explicit meaning.";i:47;s:27:"What does connotative mean.";i:48;s:113:"Information and translations of connotative in the most comprehensive dictionary definitions resource on the web.";i:49;s:129:"It is this denotative meaning students learn in foreign language classes so they will know the word chaise means chair in French.";i:50;s:187:"However of greater importance particularly in advertising is the connotative definition the definition each individual conjures up in rher mind in response to hearing or reading the word.";i:51;s:135:"Perceptual opportunities POs are Fencotts term for his theory on how to understand in-game objects connotative and denotative meanings.";i:52;s:74:"A chair is a chair but a chair can also be a weapon within the game world.";i:53;s:65:"Clive Fencott Jo Clay Mike Lockyer and Paul Massey Game Invaders.";i:54;s:47:"The Theory and Understanding of Computer Games.";i:55;s:56:"Whats the difference between connotation and denotation.";i:56;s:109:"In short denotation is the standard definition of a word whereas connotation is the feeling evoked by a word.";i:57;s:22:"Read on to learn more.";}}